Minister of Finance and Planning, Dr Mwigulu Nchemba said in Dodoma that the Government targets to boost its Growth Domestic Product (GDP) from the current 4.7 per cent to 5.3 per cent by 2023. Tabling the reports on the 2021 State of Economy as well as the National Development Plan 2022/23 in the Parliament, the government is determined to maintain inflation within a single digit range of an average of 3.0 to 7.0 per cent. In his presentation, Dr Mwigulu added that Tanzania targets to boost domestic revenue collection to 14.9 percent of GDP in 2022/23 and raise tax revenue to 11.7 per cent of GDP in 2022/23. Dr Nchemba noted that the state also intends to get a foreign exchange reserve at the rate that will enable the country to meet import demands for the minimum of four months.